<div class="c230_113">
<div id="v230.113.1"><span class="H1984 s">Praise</span><span class="H3050 s"> ye the LORD</span><span class="H1984 s">. Praise</span><span class="H5650 s">, O ye servants</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span><span class="H1984 s">, praise</span><span class="H8034 s"> the name</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (Praise ye…: Heb. Hallelujah)</span></div>
<div id="v230.113.2"><span class="H1288 s">Blessed</span><span class="H8034 s"> be the name</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the LORD</span><span class="H6258 s"> from this time forth</span><span class="H5704 s"> and for</span><span class="H5769 s"> evermore</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.113.3"><span class="H4217 s">From the rising</span><span class="H8121 s"> of the sun</span><span class="H3996 s"> unto the going down</span><span class="H3068 s"> of the same the LORD'S</span><span class="H8034 s"> name</span><span class="H1984 s"> <i>is</i> to be praised</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.113.4"><span class="H3068 s">The LORD</span><span class="H7311 s"> <i>is</i> high</span><span class="H1471 s"> above all nations</span><span class="H3519 s">, <i>and</i> his glory</span><span class="H8064 s"> above the heavens</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.113.5"><span class="H3068 s">Who <i>is</i> like unto the LORD</span><span class="H430 s"> our God</span><span class="H3427 s">, who dwelleth</span><span class="H1361 s"> on high</span>, <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (dwelleth…: Heb. exalteth himself to dwell)</span></div>
<div id="v230.113.6"><span class="H8213 s">Who humbleth</span><span class="H7200 s"> <i>himself</i> to behold</span><span class="H8064 s"> <i>the things that are</i> in heaven</span><span class="H776 s">, and in the earth</span>!</div>
<div id="v230.113.7"><span class="H6965 s">He raiseth up</span><span class="H1800 s"> the poor</span><span class="H6083 s"> out of the dust</span><span class="H7311 s">, <i>and</i> lifteth</span><span class="H34 s"> the needy</span><span class="H830 s"> out of the dunghill</span>;</div>
<div id="v230.113.8"><span class="H3427 s">That he may set</span><span class="H5081 s"> <i>him</i> with princes</span><span class="H5081 s">, <i>even</i> with the princes</span><span class="H5971 s"> of his people</span>.</div>
<div id="v230.113.9"><span class="H6135 s">He maketh the barren woman</span><span class="H3427 s"> to keep</span><span class="H1004 s"> house</span><span class="H8056 s">, <i>and to be</i> a joyful</span><span class="H517 s"> mother</span><span class="H1121 s"> of children</span><span class="H1984 s">. Praise</span><span class="H3050 s"> ye the LORD</span>. <span class="notes">Notes by the 1611 King James Bible Translators: (to keep…: Heb. to dwell in an house)</span></div></div>
